race.comment: The feature of the day here and things look to set up well for LONDON'S IMAGE (3) on the back of a strong trial win recently at Lark Hill. She tends to race well on the fresh side and only just missed in a similar race when fresh last campaign. Has plenty of early speed and can return to winning ways. WIND AND THE LION (5) has disappointed in both runs back this time in but this presents as a much better opportunity. Drawn inside here third-up into the campaign with Parnham on board. Ticks enough boxes to think a return to form is near. ALMIGHTY CLASS (6) is another who can return to form here following an impressive trial for the new stable recently. Just fair last campaign but his form prior was much better. Pike's booking is a big push for his chances. ASPHALT (7) continued to impress, even when edged out in the Carbine Club last start. Wide draw is a niggle but he's not to be discounted. COLD SHIZZLE (8) can feature in the finish once again.
